category_descriptions.Natural Robusta Coffee: Unwashed/dry-processed Robusta coffee beans, typically from Uganda, often with screen size specifications.
category_descriptions.Natural Arabica Coffee: Unroasted Arabica coffee beans processed using the natural/dry method, often specifying origin like Uganda or DRUGAR grade.
category_descriptions.Washed Arabica Coffee: Unroasted Arabica coffee beans processed using the washed/wet method, often with specific regional or grade designations like RFA or Bugisu.
category_descriptions.Screened/Graded Coffee Beans: Coffee beans sorted by screen size (e.g., SC 12, SC 15, SC 18) indicating bean size and quality grading.
category_descriptions.Screened Green Coffee: Green coffee beans sorted by screen size (e.g., SC 15, SC 18, SC 1500), applicable to both Robusta and Arabica types.
